<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="492" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d492">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/761.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Smith</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>National Bank of Haiti, as creditor of the Government, protests to this
                            Legation against the seizure of the custom house at Cape Haitien by
                            rebels, and requests the “exercise of such influence as is possible to
                            protect said creditors”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>